###
### DOCKER COMPOSE FILES - Choose One:
###
### 1. Main Setup (Recommended):
###    docker compose up -d
###    Container names: resume-frontend, resume-backend, resume-ollama
###
### 2. PostgreSQL Setup (Production-like):
###    docker compose -f docker-compose.postgresql.yml up -d
###    Container names: resume-frontend-postgres, resume-backend-postgres, resume-postgres
###
### 3. SQLite with Persistent Data:
###    docker compose -f docker-compose.sqlite.yml up -d
###    Container names: resume-frontend-sqlite, resume-backend-sqlite, resume-ollama-sqlite
###
### 4. Frontend + Backend Only:
###    docker compose -f docker-compose.frontend-backend.yml up -d
###    Container names: resume-frontend, resume-backend, resume-ollama
###
### OLLAMA LLM MODEL SETUP - REQUIRED STEP:
###
### After starting Docker Compose, you MUST pull an LLM model:
###
###    docker exec resume-ollama ollama pull mistral:latest
###
### Or use a different model based on your needs:
###    docker exec resume-ollama ollama pull tinyllama        # Fastest (800MB)
###    docker exec resume-ollama ollama pull gemma2:2b       # Balanced (1.6GB)
###    docker exec resume-ollama ollama pull phi3:mini       # High quality (2.3GB)
###    docker exec resume-ollama ollama pull qwen2.5:0.5b    # Ultra-lightweight (400MB)
###
### Check installed models:
###    docker exec resume-ollama ollama list
###
### Access Services:
###    Frontend: http://localhost:3000
###    Backend:  http://localhost:8080
###    Ollama:   http://localhost:11434/api/tags (to verify models)
###    Swagger:  http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui/index.html
