### ========================================
### NOTES FOR TESTING
### ========================================
###
### IMPORTANT: Multipart Form-Data Format
### All /generate/* and /process/* endpoints use multipart/form-data format.
### The JSON request is sent as a form field named "optimize".
### This format handles complex JSON with newlines and special characters properly.
###
### TESTING STEPS:
### 1. Start Docker Compose:
###    docker compose up -d
###
### 2. Pull an LLM model (REQUIRED - pick one):
###    docker exec resume-ollama ollama pull mistral:latest       # Recommended
###    docker exec resume-ollama ollama pull tinyllama            # Faster
###
### 3. Verify services are running:
###    # Check backend is healthy
###    curl http://localhost:8080/api/health
###
###    # Check Ollama models are loaded
###    curl -s http://localhost:11434/api/tags | grep -o '"name":"[^"]*"'
###
### 4. Choose Your API Testing Tool:
###
###    OPTION A: REST Client (VS Code Extension - Recommended for VS Code users)
###      - Install: REST Client by Huachao Mao from VS Code Extensions
###      - Open this file in VS Code
###      - Click "Send Request" button above any endpoint
###      - View response in the response panel
###
###    OPTION B: Bruno (Desktop App - Recommended for dedicated API testing)
###      - Download from: https://www.usebruno.com/
###      - Launch Bruno
###      - Click Import → Select Resume.http
###      - Click Send on any request
###      - Supports multipart/form-data perfectly
###
### 5. View results:
###    - Response shown in VS Code REST Client panel
###    - Files saved to: http://localhost:3000/files (Files Tab)
###    - Or download directly from Files Tab
###
### Request Body Format:
### All endpoints using /api/generate/* and /api/process/* require:
###   Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----FormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
###
### Structure:
###   [boundary line]
###   Content-Disposition: form-data; name="optimize"
###   [Complete JSON object as shown in examples]
###   [boundary line]--
###
### Example JSON fields in "optimize" parameter:
###   {
###     "promptType": ["interview-hr-questions"],
###     "resume": "# Full resume content as markdown or text",
###     "jobDescription": "Job posting text",
###     "company": "Company name",
###     "jobTitle": "Position title",
###     "temperature": 0.7,
###     "model": "mistral:latest",
###     "interviewerName": "Optional - for thank-you emails only"
###   }
###
### Docker Compose File Usage:
###
### Main Setup (Default - Recommended):
###   Command: docker compose up -d
###   Services: Frontend (3000), Backend (8080), Ollama (11434)
###   Database: SQLite (in-memory by default, configurable to persistent)
###   Use Case: Full development, testing, and local deployment
###
### PostgreSQL Production-like Setup:
###   Command: docker compose -f docker-compose.postgresql.yml up -d
###   Services: Frontend (3000), Backend (8080), PostgreSQL (5432)
###   Database: PostgreSQL 17 (persistent volume)
###   Use Case: Production testing, scalable deployment
###   Credentials: resume_user / resume_password
###
### SQLite with Persistent Storage:
###   Command: docker compose -f docker-compose.sqlite.yml up -d
###   Services: Frontend (3000), Backend (8080), Ollama (11434), SQLite (file-based)
###   Database: SQLite file in Docker volume (persistent)
###   Use Case: Local development with data persistence
###
### Frontend + Backend Only (No Database Service):
###   Command: docker compose -f docker-compose.frontend-backend.yml up -d
###   Services: Frontend (3000), Backend (8080), Ollama (11434)
###   Database: SQLite in-memory only
###   Use Case: Quick testing, minimal resource usage
###
### Endpoint Mapping:
### - /api/generate/* → Interview preparation and networking prompts
### - /api/process/* → Document optimization (resume, cover letter, skills)
###
### Field Mapping (JSON inside optimize parameter):
###
### Required Fields (for most endpoints):
###   - "resume" → User's resume/CV content (plain text or markdown)
###   - "jobDescription" → Job posting details
###   - "company" → Company name (for customization)
###   - "jobTitle" → Position title (for customization)
###   - "temperature" → Creativity level (0.0-1.0, 0.7 recommended)
###   - "model" → Ollama model name (e.g., "mistral:latest")
###
### Optional Fields:
###   - "interviewerName" → Add name to thank-you emails
###   - "promptType" → Specific prompt to use (see Prompt Types below)
###
### Note: Field names in JSON match Spring @SerializedName annotations
### String fields must be valid JSON strings with proper escaping
### Temperature should be between 0 and 1 (0.7 provides good balance)
### Model must be a valid Ollama model (pulled with 'ollama pull' command)
###
###
### Prompt Types Available and Their Purposes:
###
### INTERVIEW PREPARATION (Behavioral & Technical):
###   - interview-hr-questions
###     Purpose: Generate common HR interview questions
###     Returns: 5 behavioral/HR questions tailored to role
###     Use Case: Prepare for initial screening interviews
###
###   - interview-job-specific
###     Purpose: Generate technical/role-specific interview questions
###     Returns: 5 job-specific technical questions based on JD
###     Use Case: Prepare for technical interviews
###
###   - interview-reverse
###     Purpose: Questions to ask your interviewers
###     Returns: 5 thoughtful questions to ask hiring managers
###     Use Case: Show engagement and understanding during interviews
###
### PROFESSIONAL NETWORKING (Email & Message Templates):
###   - cold-email
###     Purpose: Generate professional outreach emails
###     Returns: 5 variations of unique cold emails to target contacts
###     Use Case: Networking and job search outreach
###
###   - cold-linkedin-message
###     Purpose: Generate LinkedIn connection request messages
###     Returns: 5 personalized LinkedIn messages
###     Use Case: Build professional network
###
###   - thank-you-email
###     Purpose: Post-interview thank you emails
###     Returns: 5 variations of thank-you emails
###     Use Case: Follow up after interviews (use with interviewerName field)
###
### DOCUMENT OPTIMIZATION (Resume, Cover Letter, Skills):
###   - resume
###     Purpose: Optimize resume for specific job posting
###     Returns: Tailored resume highlighting relevant experience
###     Use Case: ATS-optimized resume for target role
###
###   - cover-letter (or "cover")
###     Purpose: Generate tailored cover letter
###     Returns: Customized cover letter for job posting
###     Use Case: Professional job application letters
###
###   - skills
###     Purpose: Skills development and learning plan
###     Returns: Personalized learning roadmap for target role
###     Use Case: Identify gaps and plan skill development
